## Parameters

- [Request Body](#request-body)
- [Path and query parameters](#path-and-query-parameters)

## Request Body

Data Validation, Data Conversion, JSON schema

Request body done by post method. Fast API give us also data data validation as well.

```python
class BlogPost(BaseModel):
    title: str
    content: str
    author: str
    published: Optional[bool]   

@blog_routers.post('/new')
def create_blog(blog : BlogPost):
    print(blog.title)
    return {'data': blog}
```
now if you give title as a int then you will get an error (Unprocessable Entity).

## Path and query parameters

combine all 3 types of data in a single path.

```python
@blog_routers.post('/new/{id}')
def create_blog(blog : BlogPost, id: int = 1111, version: int = 1.0):
    print(blog.title)
    return {'id': id, 'version':version, 'data': blog}
```
## Parameter metadata

we can also add metadata for each parameter. For example : Title , description, alias, deprecation status of parameters using Query.





